<subSubSection box="[151,279,1762,1788]" pageId="13" pageNumber="444" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,719,1725,1788]" box="[151,279,1762,1788]" pageId="13" pageNumber="444">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,272,1762,1788]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[172,1416,935,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-308@14.[151,1436,921,1914]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 9. Axinoscymnus hamulatus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="444">Figs 9a–g</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="444" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1833,2041]" pageId="13" pageNumber="444">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1833,1859]" pageId="13" pageNumber="444">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Kapur et Munshi" authorityName="Kapur et Munshi" box="[572,956,1834,1860]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Axinoscymnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puttarudriahi">
<emphasis box="[572,755,1834,1860]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="444">A. puttarudriahi</emphasis>
Kapur et Munshi
</taxonomicName>
in male genitalia but can be distinguished from the latter by the black head (
<figureCitation box="[538,620,1870,1896]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[172,1416,935,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-308@14.[151,1436,921,1914]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 9. Axinoscymnus hamulatus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="444">Fig. 9c</figureCitation>
), the blackish brown pronotum and the black elytra without dark brown oval markings (
<figureCitation box="[328,411,1906,1932]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[172,1416,935,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-308@14.[151,1436,921,1914]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 9. Axinoscymnus hamulatus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="444">Fig. 9a</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName box="[464,647,1906,1932]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Axinoscymnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puttarudriahi">
<emphasis box="[464,647,1906,1932]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="444">A. puttarudriahi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, elytra are black with a single elongate oval dark brown spot on each elytron (
<figureCitation box="[246,328,1942,1968]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1583,1607]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,491,1553]" captionTargetId="figure-171@13.[151,1436,474,1567]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Axinoscymnus puttarudriahi Kapur et Munshi, 1965: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–f: 0.05 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="444">Fig. 8a</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="445" pageId="13" pageNumber="444" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1833,2041]" pageId="13" pageNumber="444">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1977,2003]" pageId="13" pageNumber="444">Description.</emphasis>
TL: 
<quantity box="[402,568,1978,2004]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.42" metricValueMax="1.48" metricValueMin="1.36" pageId="13" pageNumber="444" unit="mm" value="1.42" valueMax="1.48" valueMin="1.36">1.36–1.48 mm</quantity>
, TW: 
<quantity box="[638,804,1978,2004]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.399999999999999" metricValueMax="9.7" metricValueMin="9.1" pageId="13" pageNumber="444" unit="mm" value="0.94" valueMax="0.97" valueMin="0.91">0.91–0.97 mm</quantity>
, TH: 
<quantity box="[869,1034,1978,2004]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="6.8" metricValueMin="6.2" pageId="13" pageNumber="444" unit="mm" value="0.65" valueMax="0.68" valueMin="0.62">0.62–0.68 mm</quantity>
, TL/TW: 1.49–1.53, EL/EW: 1.15– 1.21, PL/PW: 0.48–0.55, HW/PW: 0.67–0.72, PW/EW: 0.72–0.73.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,897]" pageId="14" pageNumber="445">
Body elongate oval, moderately convex, dorsum with white pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[1017,1131,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[172,1416,935,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-308@14.[151,1436,921,1914]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 9. Axinoscymnus hamulatus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="14" pageNumber="445">Figs 9a–c</figureCitation>
). Head black, antennae and mouthparts yellowish brown (
<figureCitation box="[486,567,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[172,1416,935,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-308@14.[151,1436,921,1914]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 9. Axinoscymnus hamulatus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="14" pageNumber="445">Fig. 9c</figureCitation>
), tip of mandibles dark brown. Pronotum and scutellar shield blackish brown. Elytra black (
<figureCitation box="[303,418,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[172,1416,935,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-308@14.[151,1436,921,1914]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 9. Axinoscymnus hamulatus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="14" pageNumber="445">Figs 9a–c</figureCitation>
). Prothoracic hypomeron and prosternum blackish brown. Mesoventrite, metaventrite, and elytral epipleurae black. Legs yellowish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,897]" pageId="14" pageNumber="445">
Head with fine frontal punctures, slightly larger than eye facets, 0.5–1.5 diameters apart. Eye densely faceted, interocular distance 0.34 times of head width (
<figureCitation box="[698,784,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[172,1416,935,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-308@14.[151,1436,921,1914]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 9. Axinoscymnus hamulatus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="14" pageNumber="445">Fig. 9c</figureCitation>
). Pronotal punctures slightly larger than those on frons, 0.5–2.0 diameters apart. Surface of elytra with punctures much larger than those on pronotum, separated by 1.0–2.0 diameters.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,897]" pageId="14" pageNumber="445">
Abdomen dark brown. Abdominal postcoxal lines complete and strongly recurved, nearly reaching posterior margin of ventrite 1 (
<figureCitation box="[384,466,475,502]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[172,1416,935,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-308@14.[151,1436,921,1914]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 9. Axinoscymnus hamulatus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="14" pageNumber="445">Fig. 9d</figureCitation>
), area enclosed by the lines finely and sparsely punctate, irregularly distributed, broadly smooth along the lines; ventrite 1 with coarse punctures at middle, extremely sparse.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,897]" pageId="14" pageNumber="445">
Male genitalia. Penis short and slender, slightly broadened at base, apical 2/3 narrowing and apex blunt (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[172,1416,935,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-308@14.[151,1436,921,1914]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 9. Axinoscymnus hamulatus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="14" pageNumber="445">Fig. 9e</figureCitation>
); tegmen with penis guide widest at base, slowly narrowing to apical 1/2, then slightly curved and abruptly tapering to apex in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[455,533,619,646]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[172,1416,935,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-308@14.[151,1436,921,1914]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 9. Axinoscymnus hamulatus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="14" pageNumber="445">Fig. 9f</figureCitation>
), slightly shorter than parameres; in inner view, penis guide subtriangular, widest at base, then gradually tapering to pointed apex (
<figureCitation box="[688,771,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[172,1416,935,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-308@14.[151,1436,921,1914]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 9. Axinoscymnus hamulatus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="14" pageNumber="445">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[740,771,655,681]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="9.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="445" unit="g" value="9.0">9g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
); parameres stout and elongate oval with a few setae at apex in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[327,406,691,718]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[172,1416,935,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-308@14.[151,1436,921,1914]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 9. Axinoscymnus hamulatus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="14" pageNumber="445">Fig. 9f</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
